<p>Some facts about me:</p>

<ol>
    <li>I write code. Sometimes for money, sometimes for fun.</li>
    <li>I have a poor working memory. {% note %}I have pretty severe ADHD. I'm medicated, but meds can only do so much.{% endnote %}</li>
    <li>I tend to use a relatively small, but consistent set of tools.</li>
</ol>

<p>To compensate for my working memory deficiencies, I often try to <mark>externalize information</mark>. This is one such attempt to do so.</p>

<hr>

<h2>All posts</h2>

<ul class="feed">
{% for item in collections.feed %}
    <li class="feed-item">
        <a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.data.title or item.fileSlug }}<a>
        <span class="label content-type">{{ item.data.contentType }}</span>
        {% if item.data.snippetCategory %}
            <span class="label category-tag">{{ item.data.snippetCategory }}</span>
        {% endif%}
    </li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Browse by category</h2>

<div class="sections">
    <a class="section-link" href="/crib/">
        <h3>crib sheets</h3>
        <span class="sub-h3">quick reference notes, sans explanations</span>
    </a>
    <a class="section-link" href="/notes/">
        <h3>notes</h3>
        <span class="sub-h3">scribblings and thoughts</span>
    </a>
    <a class="section-link" href="/snippets/">
        <h3>snippets</h3>
        <span class="sub-h3">code you can copy/steal to save time</span>
    </a>
</div>